1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
ظآزOnly after bloom comes fruitظآز

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
ظآزWho says glory must fade to the pastظآز

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
ظآزOnly through thunder
do you reach the cloudsظآز

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
ظآزWho made you the crown of every peakظآز

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
ظآزI stand at the center of the stageظآز

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
ظآزMy shadow is pinned against the wallظآز

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
ظآزFacing the light earns every medalظآز

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
ظآزLittle birds,
save your needless peckingظآز

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
ظآزThe open sky rises highظآز

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
ظآزWhen night falls,
the moon begins to shineظآز

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
ظآزI stand in the heart of these landsظآز

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
ظآزMy shadow bears no crown or robeظآز

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
ظآزThen I know truth needs no disguiseظآز

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
ظآزThe green hills see me as I amظآز

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
ظآزLike dew, lightning,
and moon on the riverظآز

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
ظآزShowing me exactly who I amظآز

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,792
=Episode 46=

19
00:01:38,439 --> 00:01:39,640
You won't have a chance.

20
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:40,960
Uncle Sanyuan! Uncle!

21
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:42,080
- Call me uncle?
- Sanyuan!

22
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:42,919
How ridiculous!

23
00:01:42,919 --> 00:01:43,799
Don't act recklessly.

24
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:46,720
With a few bucks and a beat-up car,
and you think you're hot stuff?

25
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:47,960
You've got your eye on Qin'e?

26
00:01:48,199 --> 00:01:51,240
Uncle, that's not a beat-up car.
It cost over a million!

27
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:52,079
So what then?

28
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,600
Do you believe I can
turn it into scrap metal today?

29
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:56,280
- No!
- Uncle Sanyuan!

30
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,160
- I'll smash it!
- No!

31
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,879
I-I was wrong, okay?

32
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,440
Well...

33
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:01,399
I'm here to get your opinion.

34
00:02:01,399 --> 00:02:01,960
My opinion?

35
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:03,879
I don't agree. What then?

36
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:06,960
Uncle, I have free time now.

37
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,359
I can take good care of Qin'e.

38
00:02:08,359 --> 00:02:09,920
I could do better than Liu Hongbing.

39
00:02:10,439 --> 00:02:12,039
How dare you say that?

40
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,159
Go find a mirror to look at yourself.

41
00:02:14,496 --> 00:02:16,119
You look like a roasted sweet potato.

42
00:02:16,119 --> 00:02:18,159
How dare you compare
yourself to Hongbing?

43
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:19,159
Look at you, how timid!

44
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:25,024
You...

45
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,079
A piece of trash!

46
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:43,799
How am I worse than him?

47
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,560
He had a car. Well, I have a car too.

48
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,840
He had time to pester Qin'e all day.

49
00:02:48,959 --> 00:02:50,319
Now I have time too.

50
00:02:50,319 --> 00:02:51,640
I can go pester Qin'e too.

51
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:54,760
If you dare pester Qin'e again,
I'll break your legs!

52
00:02:55,159 --> 00:02:56,719
When did Hongbing ever pester Qin'e?

53
00:02:57,799 --> 00:03:00,159
They grew up together and were in love.

54
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,480
Unlike a piece of trash like you.

55
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,439
Are we talking about the same person?

56
00:03:05,079 --> 00:03:06,560
You, get lost! Shut your mouth.

57
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:09,040
If you dare pester Qin'e

58
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,719
and ruin her reputation... Listen,

59
00:03:10,719 --> 00:03:11,959
I'll fight you to the death.

60
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,040
Get lost.

61
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,079
Go do what you should.

62
00:03:30,760 --> 00:03:31,480
Are you okay?

63
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:36,959
Mr. Qin.

64
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:39,400
Sorry you had to see that.

65
00:03:42,239 --> 00:03:43,400
A total loss of dignity.

66
00:03:44,919 --> 00:03:46,080
A total loss of dignity.

67
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:50,960
I am a man of honor.

68
00:03:52,039 --> 00:03:53,639
But what can I do?

69
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,639
The troupe needs money for everything.

70
00:03:56,639 --> 00:03:58,520
We need new costumes.

71
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,000
The theater needs renovation.

72
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,479
We're about to recruit new trainees.

73
00:04:02,479 --> 00:04:06,479
The dorm and the teachers,
everything needs money.

74
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:11,400
We're a state-run troupe,
but we have to be self-sufficient.

75
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,120
For just one show, the performance fees
alone cost tens of thousands.

76
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,919
We might not break even
from ticket sales.

77
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,039
But someone has
to keep these operas alive.

78
00:04:20,479 --> 00:04:22,400
Otherwise, no one will listen to them.

79
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,240
Qinqiang opera has a history
of thousands of years. I can't ruin it.

80
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:28,000
You're overthinking it.

81
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,759
You don't have that kind of power.

82
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,039
Just focus on being
a good troupe leader.

83
00:04:38,639 --> 00:04:39,639
Mr. Qin.

84
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,360
I've let you down.

85
00:04:43,639 --> 00:04:45,599
The inscription you gave me,

86
00:04:45,599 --> 00:04:48,240
"A talented man
must not waste his time."

87
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,000
Look at how much time I've wasted.

88
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:51,879
Come on.

89
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:52,759
Don't cry.

90
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:55,280
Don't let others see you.

91
00:04:55,759 --> 00:04:57,280
Or, how can you lead the troupe?

92
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,159
I don't cry.

93
00:05:07,639 --> 00:05:08,240
I don't cry.

94
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,639
Then show me your new script.

95
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,199
Why was Sissy Xue beaten?

96
00:05:23,199 --> 00:05:24,800
You tell me why.

97
00:05:25,599 --> 00:05:27,960
Why did Yi Qin'e stop singing
and start managing costumes?

98
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,159
Why?

99
00:05:29,759 --> 00:05:30,759
Why?

100
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,800
Because Sissy Xue abused
his power for personal revenge.

101
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,759
Personal revenge?

102
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:40,159
Sissy Xue wanted to pursue Yi Qin'e,

103
00:05:40,159 --> 00:05:42,400
but she didn't agree.

104
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,680
So he demoted her
to the costume department.

105
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,960
Impossible. Where did you hear that?

106
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,240
I heard that she didn't want to sing,

107
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,159
and Sissy Xue tried to talk her into it?

108
00:05:51,919 --> 00:05:54,120
Of course, he had to talk her into it.

109
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,360
But who knows how he did it?

110
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,439
Do you know? Or do I?

111
00:05:57,759 --> 00:05:59,199
What if something else's involved?

112
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:04,199
It must be true.

113
00:06:04,199 --> 00:06:05,519
Even the police came.

114
00:06:07,639 --> 00:06:08,920
Sissy Xue had that intention?

115
00:06:10,199 --> 00:06:11,399
Here, Qin'e. Have some water.

116
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:15,759
I knew I couldn't keep this from you.

117
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,720
Actually, it's nothing.

118
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:20,040
Look, over these years,
rumors are all around.

119
00:06:20,639 --> 00:06:21,560
Don't take it to heart.

120
00:06:22,639 --> 00:06:24,920
Who's causing trouble? Do I know them?

121
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,319
You definitely know them.

122
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:29,000
(Liu Situan, Guangsha Construction Co., Ltd.)
That fat guy who looks like a bear,

123
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,759
Liu Situan.

124
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:34,120
Originally, he said
to book the whole venue.

125
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,040
It went fine at first,

126
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,600
but one day,

127
00:06:37,319 --> 00:06:39,839
I wondered if he suddenly went crazy.

128
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:41,240
He rushed over and caused trouble.

129
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:41,879
You know?

130
00:06:41,879 --> 00:06:42,920
Look what he did to me.

131
00:07:04,672 --> 00:07:06,112
(Liu Situan,
Guangsha Construction Co., Ltd.)

132
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,543
(Provincial Troupe Qinqiang Youth Actor Trainee Class,
Enrollment Exam Registration)

133
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,519
Sir.

134
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:04,920
What do you want?

135
00:08:05,439 --> 00:08:07,639
How much for a phone call?

136
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:10,000
Local calls: fifty cents.
Long distance: one yuan.

137
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,360
Uncle Hu?

138
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,839
Not five hundred. Fifty cents.

139
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:19,279
Uncle Hu.

140
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,439
I'm Song Yu.

141
00:08:24,639 --> 00:08:25,560
Song Yu?

142
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:31,160
What are you here for?

143
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:33,199
I came for the trainee class.

144
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:34,920
I want to sing opera.

145
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:39,040
She's for the trainee class audition.

146
00:08:39,959 --> 00:08:41,000
Let her stay with you.

147
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:43,319
It's improper to stay at my place.

148
00:08:43,319 --> 00:08:44,519
Or, I won't trouble you.

149
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:48,639
Besides, she's Master Song's kid.
You should look after her.

150
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,079
Alright, I'm leaving.

151
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:56,759
If you need anything,
come to me or Aunt Hua.

152
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,519
Call her Granny Hua.

153
00:09:02,759 --> 00:09:04,360
Forget it. Aunt Hua sounds just fine.

154
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:08,920
Goodbye, Uncle Hu.

155
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,600
Where's Song Yu?

156
00:09:41,839 --> 00:09:42,759
Stay at Laidi's place.

157
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:44,680
Is Laidi okay with that?

158
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,240
She has to be.

159
00:09:46,759 --> 00:09:49,199
You are just making trouble
for both of them.

160
00:09:49,199 --> 00:09:50,920
Someone needs to fix her attitude.

161
00:09:51,439 --> 00:09:54,800
You just test every cloud,
no matter rain or shine, huh?

162
00:09:55,319 --> 00:09:58,000
Even if it doesn't rain,
I'll let it stir up a storm.

163
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,920
She just wants some peace.

164
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:01,639
Why should she?

165
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,519
Why now?

166
00:10:04,079 --> 00:10:06,279
Whatever we do,
we need to know our limits.

167
00:10:06,519 --> 00:10:07,519
Time to perform, perform.

168
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:09,000
Time to sell papers, sell papers.

169
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:11,320
Why's no one playing pool today?

170
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,320
Come on, let's play a game.

171
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:15,200
No.

172
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,639
You can't beat me anyway.

173
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,960
Come on. It's to drum up business.

174
00:10:21,399 --> 00:10:22,080
I'll break first.

175
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:27,720
In.

176
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,360
In.

177
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,840
Do you have a photo of your dad?

178
00:10:57,399 --> 00:10:58,000
Yes.

179
00:10:59,519 --> 00:11:00,399
Put it out.

180
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,000
Can I?

181
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,720
I miss him too, actually.

182
00:11:33,879 --> 00:11:35,879
Tomorrow morning, we'll steam buns.

183
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,160
Okay.

184
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:46,200
(Yi Qin'e knows Hu Sanyuan's plan.)

185
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:49,639
(He wants Song Yu to give her a push.)

186
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,519
(But what could Song Yu do?)

187
00:13:53,279 --> 00:13:55,776
(Yi Qin'e sees Song Yu's grief)

188
00:13:55,776 --> 00:13:57,480
(and great caution.)

189
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,919
(She doesn't even know
what to say to Song Yu.)

190
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,080
(They are the same.)

191
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:05,159
(Both on that day,)

192
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:09,960
(a piece of their souls
was taken forever.)

193
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,600
I know why my uncle
brought Song Yu to me.

194
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,000
I just told Master Song too.

195
00:14:49,279 --> 00:14:50,919
Whether she passes the audition or not,

196
00:14:51,639 --> 00:14:54,399
I'll keep her close
and take good care of her.

197
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,039
(Tomb of Liu Hongbing)
You'd be happy, right?

198
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,039
You would.

199
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:09,799
I know you wanted
to make me happy all your life

200
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:12,559
(Liu Hongbing)
and wanted what's best for me.

201
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:22,279
But as for teaching her opera,

202
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,519
what should I do?

203
00:15:27,399 --> 00:15:28,759
I wish you were here.

204
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:30,600
You always had solutions.

205
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:35,919
Right.

206
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,000
I would cry now.

207
00:15:41,859 --> 00:15:46,115
(Tomb of Liu Hongbing,
Tomb of Beloved Son Liu Yi)

208
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:49,080
Today,

209
00:15:49,559 --> 00:15:50,960
I went to Baxian Temple again.

210
00:15:51,519 --> 00:15:52,720
Got a fortune-telling.

211
00:15:53,879 --> 00:15:56,279
Palm, face, and birth chart.

212
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:59,399
He said Wealth Star favors me this year.

213
00:16:00,399 --> 00:16:03,519
If not for that moron
withholding my money,

214
00:16:03,759 --> 00:16:05,639
I'd be rich by now.

215
00:16:05,639 --> 00:16:07,320
I'd already be a millionaire.

216
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:11,200
Fate isn't in your face,
hands, or birth charts,

217
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:13,440
but in your own heart.

218
00:16:17,679 --> 00:16:21,480
Where else could I find
someone as clear-headed as you?

219
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,120
I didn't curse him.

220
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:30,240
Me neither.

221
00:16:32,759 --> 00:16:33,559
Caixiang.

222
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,159
Well,

223
00:16:35,159 --> 00:16:37,840
when I have money,
you can come to my place.

224
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:40,919
You can do or get whatever you want.

225
00:16:40,919 --> 00:16:42,200
I can grant you anything.

226
00:16:42,799 --> 00:16:43,720
No need.

227
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,120
I'll earn whatever I want.
I don't rely on others.

228
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:49,480
True. That moron is not reliable.

229
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:51,200
Otherwise, why would he sit so far away?

230
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,799
I'm telling you,
you broke our agreement.

231
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,080
We agreed on one week.

232
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,879
It's not even time yet.
Why come to press me?

233
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,559
Let's get this straight.

234
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,600
I'm not here to press you.

235
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,440
I'm just here chatting with Caixiang.

236
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:14,080
(Yu Tang Chun, a Qinqiang opera)
ظآزMadam Pi changed her expression upon seeing itظآز

237
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:19,639
ظآزShe said the convicted woman
killed her husbandظآز

238
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:26,080
ظآزShe gathered neighbors
and the local constableظآز

239
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:30,919
ظآزTo drag and pull meظآز

240
00:17:31,559 --> 00:17:35,519
ظآزPulling and tugging
all the way to the yamenظآز

241
00:17:35,519 --> 00:17:37,159
The first court session?

242
00:17:41,279 --> 00:17:45,960
ظآزThe first session was fairly judgedظآز

243
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,399
The second session?

244
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:53,080
ظآزIn the second session,
he changed his mindظآز

245
00:17:53,399 --> 00:17:55,000
How?

246
00:17:55,000 --> 00:18:00,799
ظآزThe magistrate took
a thousand taels in bribesظآز

247
00:18:00,799 --> 00:18:06,279
ظآزAnd eight hundred silver pieces
were split among the whole yamenظآز

248
00:18:06,879 --> 00:18:12,639
ظآزWhen I came before the court,
they pinched my fingers firstظآز

249
00:18:12,639 --> 00:18:14,440
ظآزMy lordظآز

250
00:18:14,440 --> 00:18:15,000
Speak!

251
00:18:17,799 --> 00:18:18,559
Who are you?

252
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,679
Here for trainee class audition, right?

253
00:18:23,639 --> 00:18:24,480
You too?

254
00:18:25,039 --> 00:18:27,480
No, I'm back to take
the college entrance exam.

255
00:18:28,039 --> 00:18:29,240
I live in the next unit.

256
00:18:29,679 --> 00:18:32,000
Then what are you doing here?

257
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,519
I'm waiting for my buddy.
He lives upstairs from you.

258
00:18:35,039 --> 00:18:37,439
And what were you singing?

259
00:18:37,439 --> 00:18:39,240
You're so noisy
that I can't hear the music.

260
00:18:39,759 --> 00:18:41,359
How did your master teach you?

261
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,319
Nobody sings like that anymore.

262
00:18:43,759 --> 00:18:44,440
Who said so?

263
00:18:44,759 --> 00:18:45,680
Me.

264
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,480
What do you know?

265
00:18:46,839 --> 00:18:48,440
I know everything about Qinqiang opera.

266
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:51,880
You know it that well?

267
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,440
Why don't you audition?

268
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:57,160
Me? I take after my dad.

269
00:18:57,519 --> 00:18:59,519
I'm tone-deaf. Can't sing opera.

270
00:19:00,039 --> 00:19:01,359
And I don't like singing opera.

271
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,480
I'm going to be a director someday.

272
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:06,119
Qinqiang opera has a history
of over a thousand years.

273
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:08,039
That's how my mom sang
when she learned opera.

274
00:19:08,039 --> 00:19:09,640
That's how my mom's master learned too.

275
00:19:10,079 --> 00:19:11,744
And people are still
learning it that way.

276
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:15,519
When I become a director someday,
I'll make some changes.

277
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:17,640
Your master is Yi Qin'e, right?

278
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:19,119
My mom said,

279
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:21,039
if she kept singing,

280
00:19:21,039 --> 00:19:22,559
she can even establish her own style.

281
00:19:23,119 --> 00:19:24,240
Too bad she stopped singing.

282
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,119
Y-Your mom studied opera too?

283
00:19:26,119 --> 00:19:27,960
My mom was way more
famous than Yi Qin'e.

284
00:19:28,279 --> 00:19:29,720
My mom even released records.

285
00:19:30,680 --> 00:19:32,079
You're bragging.

286
00:19:32,079 --> 00:19:33,039
Bragging?

287
00:19:33,039 --> 00:19:34,359
Come with me and I'll prove it.

288
00:19:37,799 --> 00:19:39,200
This is an antique.

289
00:19:39,839 --> 00:19:41,480
Out of print. You can't buy it.

290
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:44,799
If I had a record player,
I could let you hear it.

291
00:19:45,279 --> 00:19:46,319
But there isn't one here.

292
00:19:47,839 --> 00:19:48,480
Pretty, right?

293
00:19:49,039 --> 00:19:50,528
When my mom was young,

294
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,480
she was the belle
of the provincial troupe.

295
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,400
Her voice was so bright.

296
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:57,119
You could even hear her
in the Qinling Mountains once she sang.

297
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:00,559
If she'd kept singing, Yi Qin'e
wouldn't have stood a chance.

298
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:01,984
This...

299
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,039
Mom, you're back.

300
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:07,079
Thought you went to Xiaowei's place.

301
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:08,799
Xiaowei wasn't home.

302
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,519
Who's this?

303
00:20:10,519 --> 00:20:11,400
Song Yu.

304
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,599
Lives downstairs from Xiaowei.

305
00:20:12,599 --> 00:20:14,200
Downstairs from Xiaowei?

306
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:14,960
Hello, ma'am.

307
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,559
I'm from Ningzhou,
here for trainee class audition.

308
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,759
Yi Qin'e is my aunt.

309
00:20:19,759 --> 00:20:21,200
Yi Qin'e is your aunt?

310
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,400
What? Is she teaching you?

311
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:25,240
What did she teach?

312
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:26,279
Sing some lines for me.

313
00:20:26,839 --> 00:20:27,359
Okay.

314
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:38,599
ظآزWest Lake is still the sameظآز

315
00:20:39,279 --> 00:20:40,799
Louder.

316
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:41,960
Be confident.

317
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:47,000
ظآزWorn and wearyظآز

318
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,440
What are you singing?

319
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:50,240
Is this what Yi Qin'e taught you?

320
00:20:51,359 --> 00:20:53,279
I learned it from her tapes.

321
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:55,200
The tape teacher?

322
00:20:55,839 --> 00:20:56,519
Alright.

323
00:20:56,519 --> 00:20:58,160
I'll take some mangoes to Xiaowei's mom.

324
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,480
Offer Song Yu something to eat.

325
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,079
Okay.

326
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,039
Goodbye, ma'am.

327
00:21:04,279 --> 00:21:05,319
What did I tell you?

328
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,759
You sang it wrong, right?

329
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:10,279
Was it wrong?

330
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:35,880
You took an apprentice?

331
00:21:37,759 --> 00:21:38,880
That Song Yu.

332
00:21:40,559 --> 00:21:41,359
What's wrong?

333
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:42,759
Do you sing now?

334
00:21:44,599 --> 00:21:45,319
No.

335
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,599
If you teach, teach properly.
That kid has good potential.

336
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,640
Honestly, it's a pity
you don't sing anymore.

337
00:21:58,319 --> 00:22:01,000
If I hadn't stopped for so many years
and couldn't pick it back up,

338
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,160
I'd still want to sing.

339
00:22:19,839 --> 00:22:21,039
Wash your hands and eat.

340
00:22:28,559 --> 00:22:29,440
Where did you go?

341
00:22:30,519 --> 00:22:33,480
I went for a walk downstairs.

342
00:22:36,799 --> 00:22:38,240
Went to Aunt Gong's place, right?

343
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,400
What did you go for?

344
00:22:44,599 --> 00:22:47,480
T-To see the records
she released before.

345
00:22:50,319 --> 00:22:51,480
Sit down and eat.

346
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,480
Sit down and eat.

347
00:23:03,559 --> 00:23:04,680
What did you talk about?

348
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:12,759
N-Nothing much.

349
00:23:13,359 --> 00:23:14,359
You sang, right?

350
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:19,359
Yes.

351
00:23:25,519 --> 00:23:26,279
Let's eat.

352
00:23:27,480 --> 00:23:28,839
You eat these two chicken legs.

353
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:31,400
Later, take that half chicken
to Uncle Hu.

354
00:23:47,519 --> 00:23:48,880
(If you teach, teach properly.)

355
00:23:50,039 --> 00:23:51,279
(That kid has good potential.)

356
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:05,680
Today,

357
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,319
Liu Hongbing

358
00:24:08,319 --> 00:24:11,839
has gifted everyone
a batch of new practice uniforms

359
00:24:12,319 --> 00:24:15,000
as a reward
for your brilliant performances.

360
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,440
I watched your performances.

361
00:24:18,359 --> 00:24:20,720
I watched every single one.

362
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:24,279
You guys are the absolute best!

363
00:24:43,799 --> 00:24:44,720
Who is it?

364
00:24:45,359 --> 00:24:46,400
I'm coming in.

365
00:24:51,799 --> 00:24:53,039
Change and come with me.

366
00:25:01,839 --> 00:25:02,559
Follow my lead.

367
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,640
Toes pointing forward.

368
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,039
Sink your breath to the Dantian.

369
00:25:07,519 --> 00:25:09,799
Sink your shoulders down.

370
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,160
Relax.

371
00:25:20,359 --> 00:25:21,160
Do it.

372
00:25:22,599 --> 00:25:24,279
Yes, relax your facial muscles.

373
00:25:24,599 --> 00:25:27,599
Before each time you sing,
breathe the air down to your Dantian.

374
00:25:28,359 --> 00:25:29,519
Breathe in.

375
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:32,200
When you exhale, exhale slowly.

376
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,680
Before singing, open
your chest cavity, head cavity,

377
00:25:36,680 --> 00:25:38,400
nasal cavity, and oral cavity.

378
00:25:38,720 --> 00:25:39,759
Here, relax.

379
00:25:40,039 --> 00:25:41,279
Breathe down.

380
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,799
Inhale slowly.

381
00:25:43,799 --> 00:25:44,880
Come on, inhale.

382
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:49,200
The slower you exhale, the better.

383
00:25:49,519 --> 00:25:50,759
Exhale slowly.

384
00:25:51,839 --> 00:25:52,759
Hold it here.

385
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:56,359
Try singing a couple of lines.

386
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,079
S-Sing what?

387
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,079
Anything.

388
00:26:02,119 --> 00:26:03,519
Remember the method.

389
00:26:04,039 --> 00:26:06,000
Sink your breath
to the Dantian and relax.

390
00:26:07,799 --> 00:26:13,759
ظآزWest Lakeظآز

391
00:26:13,759 --> 00:26:14,480
Wrong.

392
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:16,839
Relax your chest cavity.

393
00:26:19,359 --> 00:26:25,839
ظآزWest Lakeظآز

394
00:26:25,839 --> 00:26:26,599
Wrong.

395
00:26:27,799 --> 00:26:29,160
Think it through before you sing.

396
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:31,720
Then,

397
00:26:32,559 --> 00:26:34,119
could you make an example for me?

398
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:41,799
You sing along to this.

399
00:26:43,552 --> 00:26:51,480
ظآزWest Lake is still the sameظآز

400
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:52,559
What are you doing?

401
00:26:52,559 --> 00:26:53,240
Aunt Hua.

402
00:26:53,799 --> 00:26:55,160
I'm teaching her to sing opera.

403
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,400
She's teaching me.

404
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,440
She's teaching you?

405
00:26:59,519 --> 00:27:00,839
Is that how I taught you?

406
00:27:04,150 --> 00:27:08,480
ظآزBut my haggard selfظآز

407
00:27:10,559 --> 00:27:11,359
Sit and watch.

408
00:27:14,279 --> 00:27:15,119
Sing some lines.

409
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:24,279
ظآزWest Lakeظآز

410
00:27:24,279 --> 00:27:24,960
Wrong.

411
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,640
She is right.

412
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:32,150
Singing opera requires vocal ability.

413
00:27:32,448 --> 00:27:34,519
But you can't rely on
shouting with a raw voice.

414
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:36,200
Then it isn't singing opera.

415
00:27:36,759 --> 00:27:37,960
It still needs rhythm.

416
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:39,599
Listen to me sing it once.

417
00:27:43,799 --> 00:27:53,799
ظآزWest Lake is still the sameظآز

418
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,279
Here's today's newspaper.

419
00:28:03,079 --> 00:28:04,119
Why so early today?

420
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:06,519
Nowadays, overtime is required.

421
00:28:07,319 --> 00:28:08,119
Okay, thanks.

422
00:28:08,359 --> 00:28:09,279
Alright. I'm off.

423
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:16,039
Time to eat.

424
00:28:16,039 --> 00:28:16,960
I bought breakfast.

425
00:28:20,039 --> 00:28:21,880
Where did you three go
so early this morning?

426
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,480
To warm up her voice.

427
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:24,880
She sang?

428
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:26,144
Yes.

429
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,200
Who did it?

430
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:28,400
Aunt Hua.

431
00:28:29,839 --> 00:28:30,960
Live at Qin'e's place,

432
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,920
then learn from her.
Why learn from Aunt Hua?

433
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,279
And you.

434
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,519
Did you promise
Master Song to teach her?

435
00:28:36,519 --> 00:28:37,119
No.

436
00:28:37,519 --> 00:28:39,160
Whoever promised should teach.

437
00:28:39,799 --> 00:28:42,240
- I didn't promise either.
- What?

438
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,359
You did promise Master Song
and I heard it clearly.

439
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,319
Since you promised, teach properly.

440
00:28:46,319 --> 00:28:48,640
If she fails, you'd tell Master Song.

441
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,759
Watch the stall. I'm stepping out.

442
00:28:50,759 --> 00:28:51,599
Where are you going?

443
00:28:52,119 --> 00:28:53,024
Buy lottery tickets.

444
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,200
They say the first batch
has high winning odds.

445
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:02,720
Don't just stand there.
Go do what you need to do.

446
00:29:03,519 --> 00:29:07,240
ظآزOne day when Father returns,
he will clear this injusticeظآز

447
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:10,440
ظآزHe'll slay the villain to avenge
his daughter and right the wrongsظآز

448
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:31,599
ظآزHere I weep, bowing low
with tears streamingظآز

449
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:47,200
Next one, come.

450
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:50,680
Show your real skills to Mr. Qin.

451
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:55,960
ظآزOld father, don'tظآز

452
00:30:07,599 --> 00:30:10,599
Mr. Qin, how was that one?

453
00:30:11,359 --> 00:30:12,720
Not worse than Yi Qin'e, right?

454
00:30:13,359 --> 00:30:14,279
We have better ones.

455
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,480
Don't worry.

456
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:19,359
For your script,
I'll use only the best team.

457
00:30:19,359 --> 00:30:20,119
Shh.

458
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,599
If you see anyone fits, tell me.

459
00:30:25,599 --> 00:30:42,039
ظآزWith Pinggui, I need no top scholarظآز

460
00:30:43,279 --> 00:30:44,440
Listen carefully.

461
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:48,880
If you see anyone fits, tell me.

462
00:30:57,119 --> 00:30:59,079
ظآزAncient peopleظآز

463
00:31:00,519 --> 00:31:02,480
I've heard five people sing it.

464
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:05,680
But my wife said none are quite right.

465
00:31:07,599 --> 00:31:10,440
Mr. Qin, how did you become my uncle?

466
00:31:11,599 --> 00:31:14,440
Because no one
can sing this script well,

467
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:15,720
except you.

468
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:16,960
I can't sing it either.

469
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:22,559
My wife didn't perform opera,

470
00:31:22,559 --> 00:31:25,640
but she had watched it her whole life.
She understood it.

471
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:27,920
Before she passed, she told me

472
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:31,279
this is the best script
she's ever seen me write.

473
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:34,519
She asked me to finish
the ending properly and not to ruin it.

474
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:38,400
If I truly can't find anyone to sing it,

475
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,799
just let me take this to my grave.

476
00:31:41,319 --> 00:31:43,359
In the next life, she'll find me

477
00:31:43,359 --> 00:31:44,079
and perform it.

478
00:31:44,079 --> 00:31:44,960
Mr. Qin.

479
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:48,000
Did she really say that?

480
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:50,160
Life is like a play.

481
00:31:51,279 --> 00:31:52,759
Who can tell what's real or fake?

482
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,279
As for me,

483
00:31:57,519 --> 00:31:58,559
I...

484
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,839
I can't finish the ending.

485
00:32:01,759 --> 00:32:04,480
As for you, you can't perform.

486
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:09,000
But both of us don't know

487
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:12,920
how to express this feeling.

488
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:17,640
This isn't urgent.

489
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:21,240
I would live quite a few more days.

490
00:32:23,279 --> 00:32:24,599
Let's take it slow.

491
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:28,000
Who can say

492
00:32:29,559 --> 00:32:30,640
this isn't a solution?

493
00:32:58,079 --> 00:33:09,559
ظآزBut my haggard self
can't face this autumn sceneryظآز

494
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:19,640
ظآزFrost tints maples, chilling the woodsظآز

495
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:23,400
Stop singing along with the tapes.

496
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:24,768
Why?

497
00:33:25,559 --> 00:33:27,359
Qinqiang opera is about freedom.

498
00:33:27,799 --> 00:33:28,839
Singing along with tapes,

499
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:31,400
over time, you'll just echo others,

500
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:32,720
and lose your own style,

501
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,359
without your souls.

502
00:33:35,279 --> 00:33:36,160
Then you teach me.

503
00:33:36,559 --> 00:33:37,440
Have Qin'e teach you.

504
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,480
She sings better than me.

505
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,559
But she refuses to sing.

506
00:33:42,559 --> 00:33:43,759
She will sing.

507
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:45,240
When she figures it out

508
00:33:45,599 --> 00:33:46,599
and becomes lively again,

509
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,079
she'll sing naturally.

510
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:50,160
If you want to practice, do it yourself.

511
00:33:51,599 --> 00:33:53,079
What's wrong with these people?

512
00:33:53,359 --> 00:33:55,119
Everyone criticizes,
yet nobody teaches me.

513
00:33:58,000 --> 00:33:59,279
Hungry? Then eat.

514
00:33:59,680 --> 00:34:00,608
Don't wait for Qin'e.

515
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:02,759
Not hungry.

516
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:05,599
I can see you drooling.

517
00:34:07,799 --> 00:34:08,559
You're back.

518
00:34:09,119 --> 00:34:10,000
Aunt Hua.

519
00:34:10,279 --> 00:34:11,480
Perfect timing.

520
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,920
Go wash your hands for dinner.

521
00:34:14,359 --> 00:34:16,119
Eat now. Qin'e is home.

522
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,160
Try these ribs.

523
00:34:22,160 --> 00:34:22,799
Delicious.

524
00:34:23,359 --> 00:34:24,119
They're all yours.

525
00:34:24,519 --> 00:34:25,400
Aunt Hua.

526
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:26,839
Come here.

527
00:34:28,319 --> 00:34:29,240
You eat.

528
00:34:31,119 --> 00:34:31,680
What's wrong?

529
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:42,160
I want to talk to you about Song Yu.

530
00:34:44,279 --> 00:34:45,119
What's wrong?

531
00:34:46,359 --> 00:34:47,480
Right now,

532
00:34:49,240 --> 00:34:50,519
I really can't teach her.

533
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,680
I'm not asking you to teach her now.

534
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,160
Remember?

535
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:58,160
Back then, you'd already won awards
and made it to the provincial troupe,

536
00:34:58,160 --> 00:34:59,759
yet I was selling liangpi by then.

537
00:34:59,759 --> 00:35:01,359
And you still learned opera from me.

538
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,240
Take it easy.

539
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:14,920
I know what you and my uncle want.

540
00:35:16,279 --> 00:35:19,079
I also know you're all worried about me.

541
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:20,920
But right now,

542
00:35:22,839 --> 00:35:24,200
I truly can't do it.

543
00:35:24,599 --> 00:35:25,720
You're overthinking it.

544
00:35:26,519 --> 00:35:28,920
Sing when you want to.
Don't when you don't.

545
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:32,200
When you want to sing,
no one could stop you.

546
00:35:34,119 --> 00:35:35,200
As for Song Yu,

547
00:35:36,319 --> 00:35:38,799
if you can't teach her, I'm still here.

548
00:35:42,319 --> 00:35:43,559
Actually, your uncle

549
00:35:44,519 --> 00:35:46,119
let Song Yu stay with you

550
00:35:46,639 --> 00:35:48,239
to make you two keep each other company.

551
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,559
All these years,

552
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:54,039
you've both been so lonely.

553
00:36:04,039 --> 00:36:04,880
Aunt Hua.

554
00:36:06,199 --> 00:36:07,079
Thank you.

555
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:09,199
What for?

556
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,119
Silly child.

557
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:14,280
Go wash your hands for dinner.

558
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,424
The dishes are getting cold.

559
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:16,896
Go.

560
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:54,559
Song Yu.

561
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:56,639
Song Yu.

562
00:36:59,199 --> 00:37:00,119
Having nightmares?

563
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:15,800
Sorry.

564
00:37:17,199 --> 00:37:18,280
I woke you up.

565
00:37:20,559 --> 00:37:21,519
Drink it slowly.

566
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:28,480
Do you often have nightmares?

567
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,400
I did at first.

568
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:33,719
But now I hardly have them.

569
00:37:34,639 --> 00:37:36,960
Are you nervous
because exams are coming?

570
00:37:39,039 --> 00:37:41,000
It's normal to be nervous about exams.

571
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:44,840
When I first joined the troupe,
I also faced exams.

572
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,159
There were so many people,

573
00:37:50,039 --> 00:37:51,559
and everyone had special talents.

574
00:37:52,519 --> 00:37:54,800
Only I knew nothing.

575
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,639
So my uncle had Aunt Hua teach me.

576
00:38:00,119 --> 00:38:02,000
But I couldn't bring myself to sing.

577
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:04,800
Aunt Hua even thought I was mute.

578
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,320
Then during the exam,

579
00:38:08,159 --> 00:38:11,039
I felt my feet clenching like fists.

580
00:38:13,679 --> 00:38:16,159
So I imagined the examiners as sheep,

581
00:38:17,199 --> 00:38:18,039
then I roared.

582
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:20,440
And it was over.

583
00:38:25,239 --> 00:38:26,519
At that time,

584
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,400
why couldn't you sing?

585
00:38:31,039 --> 00:38:32,559
I didn't know how. How did I sing?

586
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:34,960
Besides, I was scared.

587
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:39,039
I was so scared that I just wanted
to go home to herd sheep.

588
00:38:40,519 --> 00:38:41,719
Did you go home?

589
00:38:44,400 --> 00:38:45,159
Yes.

590
00:38:48,039 --> 00:38:50,000
But Aunt Hua caught me
and brought me back.

591
00:38:51,599 --> 00:38:52,679
Later,

592
00:38:53,760 --> 00:38:55,079
I ended up in the kitchen.

593
00:39:02,159 --> 00:39:04,280
The kitchen is fine.

594
00:39:07,679 --> 00:39:08,880
It was.

595
00:39:14,199 --> 00:39:15,400
So now,

596
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,719
are you scared?

597
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:35,039
I know you often visited me
at the orphanage.

598
00:39:37,239 --> 00:39:38,840
The director gave

599
00:39:39,559 --> 00:39:41,039
the things you brought to me.

600
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,880
At first, she said

601
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:47,360
they were donated by kind people.

602
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:50,519
Later, I found it strange.

603
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:54,320
Because donations

604
00:39:55,599 --> 00:39:58,280
are usually shared by everyone
at the orphanage.

605
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:02,199
Why would someone donate to me alone?

606
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,119
Later,

607
00:40:09,639 --> 00:40:10,679
she told me the truth.

608
00:40:16,039 --> 00:40:16,960
Sorry.

609
00:40:18,119 --> 00:40:19,559
You don't need to apologize.

610
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:24,679
Before I knew you,

611
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:27,559
my dad had already spoken about you.

612
00:40:29,559 --> 00:40:30,199
He said

613
00:40:31,079 --> 00:40:32,760
you were practically raised by him.

614
00:40:35,199 --> 00:40:37,639
He told me you sang opera beautifully,

615
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:40,599
and he was so proud.

616
00:41:21,280 --> 00:41:22,000
Master Chen.

617
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:24,320
Can this really strengthen the body?

618
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:26,719
Forty.

619
00:41:27,920 --> 00:41:30,360
Do it for forty years and you'll see.

620
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:31,480
No.

621
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,679
I'm telling you, I can't do this.

622
00:41:33,679 --> 00:41:34,760
T-This hurts terribly.

623
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:36,039
Hang in.

624
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:37,039
What for?

625
00:41:37,039 --> 00:41:39,280
Hang in, and your bones will toughen.

626
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:40,599
My bones aren't soft either.

627
00:41:41,199 --> 00:41:43,880
I suspect you were the one
who knocked this tree crooked.

628
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:46,400
Qin'e.

629
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,039
Where are you going?

630
00:41:48,679 --> 00:41:50,159
Taking her to practice singing.

631
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:52,320
Is this your apprentice?

632
00:41:53,239 --> 00:41:54,039
No.

633
00:41:57,880 --> 00:41:58,800
Qin'e.

634
00:41:59,719 --> 00:42:02,719
What's that new script Mr. Qin wrote?
Can you tell me about it?

635
00:42:03,679 --> 00:42:04,880
It's so frustrating.

636
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:07,599
I found five actresses, but he said
none of them were suitable.

637
00:42:08,159 --> 00:42:11,119
I was wondering if he wrote a play
for a Laodan role.

638
00:42:11,119 --> 00:42:13,400
So, do you think I can play it?

639
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:16,119
Wait until he shows you the script,
then you'll know.

640
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,840
But he doesn't show it to me.

641
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:28,079
ظآزWest Lakeظآز

642
00:42:28,079 --> 00:42:28,760
Wrong.

643
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:42,320
ظآزWest Lakeظآز

644
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,000
Wrong.

645
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:48,840
ظآزWest Lakeظآز

646
00:42:48,840 --> 00:42:49,599
Wrong.

647
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,280
I don't know what's wrong.

648
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:58,000
And I don't know
when I'll sing it right.

649
00:42:59,079 --> 00:43:00,079
But if I keep singing,

650
00:43:01,480 --> 00:43:03,000
then would I sing it right one day?

651
00:43:05,088 --> 00:43:07,072
(Preview)

652
00:43:08,869 --> 00:43:11,648
On TV, people give this as a gift
only during the proposal scene.

653
00:43:12,989 --> 00:43:14,029
Don't try to match us up.

654
00:43:14,469 --> 00:43:16,389
How could I possibly match you two up?

655
00:43:16,630 --> 00:43:19,190
Performing opera
is just for making a living.

656
00:43:20,069 --> 00:43:24,869
Why are my master and Qin'e so stubborn?

657
00:43:24,869 --> 00:43:28,150
I haven't sung it
for you alone yet, have I?

658
00:43:28,909 --> 00:43:30,029
ظآزWindظآز

659
00:43:30,310 --> 00:43:31,830
ظآزWindظآز

660
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

661
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

662
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
ظآزWe met and brushed pastظآز

663
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
ظآزYour shadow drifted out of sightظآز

664
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
ظآزThe stove fire blazed in my dreamظآز

665
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
ظآزLit up the tracks of pearly tearsظآز

666
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
ظآزIn my dream, water sleeves flewظآز

667
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
ظآزHiding a lifetime of loveظآز

668
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
ظآزThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stageظآز

669
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
ظآزSpring water brewed strong wineظآز

670
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
ظآزSheep moved through the valleyظآز

671
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
ظآزIt felt like a promise
from another lifeظآز

672
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

673
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

674
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
ظآزIf I chose again, I'd still roamظآز

675
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
ظآزAll over this sunlit plateauظآز

676
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
ظآزThe dream ends; the curtain fallsظآز

677
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
ظآزMoonlight washes off this stage makeupظآز

678
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
ظآزThe one in the mirror wears gray hairظآز

679
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
ظآزAlready sang all my joy and sorrowظآز

680
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
ظآزAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plainظآز
